Interface Enrollable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Course

    public interface Enrollable
    Provides behavior for objects that represent something that students can enroll in or drop out of.
    Author:
    SarahHeckman

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean canEnroll(User user)
      Returns true if there is capacity to add a user to the course and the user is not already enrolled.
      boolean drop(User user)
      Drops the student from the course.
      boolean enroll(User user)
      Enroll the user in the course if there is room.

      Returns the enrolled students as an array.
